WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.421
{"en":"--- lesson 12  Life on a desert island ","ch":"荒岛生活 "}

2
00:00:04.571 --> 00:00:10.221
{"en":"Most of us have formed an unrealistic picture of life on a desert island. ^ ","ch":"我们许多人对于荒岛生活有一种不切实际的想法。  "}

3
00:00:10.371 --> 00:00:18.110
{"en":"We sometimes imagine a desert island to be a sort of paradise where the sun always shines. ^ ","ch":"我们有时想象荒岛是阳光终日普照的天堂。  "}

4
00:00:18.260 --> 00:00:20.643
{"en":"Life there is simple and good. ^ ","ch":"在那里， 生活简单又美好。  "}

5
00:00:20.793 --> 00:00:25.633
{"en":"Ripe fruit falls from the trees and you never have to work. ^ ","ch":"成熟的水果从树上掉下来， 人们根本无需劳动。  "}

6
00:00:25.783 --> 00:00:29.394
{"en":"The other side of the picture is quite the opposite. ^ ","ch":"另一种想法恰恰相反，  "}

7
00:00:29.544 --> 00:00:32.242
{"en":"Life on a desert island is wretched. ^ ","ch":"认为荒岛生活很可怕，  "}

8
00:00:32.392 --> 00:00:40.157
{"en":"You either starve to death or live like Robinson Crusoe,  Waiting for a boat which never comes. ^ ","ch":"要么饿死， 要么像鲁滨孙那样， 天天盼船来， 却总不见船影。  "}

9
00:00:40.307 --> 00:00:44.441
{"en":"Perhaps there is an element of truth in both these pictures, ^ ","ch":"也许， 这两种想象都有可信之处。  "}

10
00:00:44.591 --> 00:00:48.229
{"en":"but few of us have had the opportunity to find out. ^ ","ch":"但很少有人能有机会去弄个究竟。  "}

11
00:00:48.379 --> 00:00:56.066
{"en":"Two men who recently spent five days on a coral island wished they had stayed there longer. ^ ","ch":"最近有两个人在一座珊瑚岛上呆了5天， 他们真希望在那儿再多呆一些日子。  "}

12
00:00:56.216 --> 00:01:02.753
{"en":"They were taking a badly damaged boat from the Virgin Islands to Miami to have it repaired. ^ ","ch":"他们驾着一条严重损坏的小船从维尔京群岛去迈阿密修理。  "}

13
00:01:02.903 --> 00:01:06.306
{"en":"During the journey,  their boat began to sink. ^ ","ch":"途中， 船开始下沉，  "}

14
00:01:06.456 --> 00:01:12.784
{"en":"They quickly loaded a small rubber dinghy with food,  matches,  and cans of beer^ ","ch":"他们迅速把食物、火柴、罐装啤酒往一只救生筏上装。  "}

15
00:01:12.934 --> 00:01:19.706
{"en":"and rowed for a few miles across the Caribbean until they arrived at a tiny coral island. ^ ","ch":"然后在加勒比海上划行了几英里， 到了一座珊瑚岛上。  "}

16
00:01:19.856 --> 00:01:27.517
{"en":"There were hardly any trees on the island and there was no water,  but this did not prove to be a problem. ^ ","ch":"岛上几乎没有一颗树， 也没有淡水， 但这不算什么问题。  "}

17
00:01:27.667 --> 00:01:31.226
{"en":"The men collected rainwater in the rubber dinghy. ^ ","ch":"他们用像皮艇蓄积雨水。  "}

18
00:01:31.376 --> 00:01:35.719
{"en":"As they had brought a spear gun with them,  they had plenty to eat. ^ ","ch":"由于他们随身带了一支捕鱼枪， 因此， 吃饭不愁。  "}

19
00:01:35.869 --> 00:01:43.190
{"en":"They caught lobster and fish every day, and,  as one of them put it 'ate like kings'. ^ ","ch":"他们天天捕捉龙虾和鱼， 正如其中一位所说， 吃得像国王一样好”。  "}

20
00:01:43.340 --> 00:01:51.550
{"en":"When a passing tanker rescued them five days later,  both men were genuinely sorry that they had to leave. ^ ","ch":"天后， 一条油轮从那儿路过， 搭救了他们。 这二位不得不离开那个荒岛时， 还真的感到遗憾呢！  "}

